abstract: Travelers entering the United States from Italy, South Korea and Iran will face new restrictions as part of efforts to curtail the spread of the coronavirus, President Donald Trump and U.S. health officials said on Saturday.
snippet: Travelers entering the United States from Italy, South Korea and Iran will face new restrictions as part of efforts to curtail the spread of the coronavirus, President Donald Trump and U.S. health officials said on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Travelers entering the United States from Italy, South Korea and Iran will face new restrictions as part of efforts to curtail the spread of the coronavirus, President Donald Trump and U.S. health officials said on Saturday.
headline_main: Trump White House Warns Americans Against Travel to South Korea, Italy
headline_print_headline: Trump White House Warns Americans Against Travel to South Korea, Italy

abstract: The activist hedge fund Elliott Management has taken a sizable stake in Twitter and called for changes at the social network.
snippet: The activist hedge fund Elliott Management has taken a sizable stake in Twitter and called for changes at the social network.
lead_paragraph: One of Wall Street’s most powerful activist hedge funds has taken a stake in Twitter and intends to shake up the social network — including by potentially calling for the replacement of its founder, Jack Dorsey, as chief executive, two people briefed on the matter said on Saturday.

abstract: President Donald Trump said additional coronavirus cases in the United States were "likely" but that the country was prepared for any circumstance, at a news conference on Saturday after reports of the first U.S. patient death from the virus.
snippet: President Donald Trump said additional coronavirus cases in the United States were "likely" but that the country was prepared for any circumstance, at a news conference on Saturday after reports of the first U.S. patient death from the virus.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump said additional coronavirus cases in the United States were "likely" but that the country was prepared for any circumstance, at a news conference on Saturday after reports of the first U.S. patient death from the virus.
headline_main: Additional U.S. Coronavirus Cases Are 'Likely,' Trump Says
headline_print_headline: Additional U.S. Coronavirus Cases Are 'Likely,' Trump Says

abstract: A person in the Seattle area died. Two others tested positive for the virus in a long term care center where dozens of people have reported feeling ill.
snippet: A person in the Seattle area died. Two others tested positive for the virus in a long term care center where dozens of people have reported feeling ill.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Concerns about the coronavirus intensified across the Pacific Northwest on Saturday, after a person from the Seattle area died and as two new cases emerged inside a nursing care center in Kirkland, Wash., where dozens of other people were reported to be feeling sick.

abstract: The United States is considering shutting the country's southern border with Mexico to control the spread of the new coronavirus, President Donald Trump said on Saturday, as his administration announced new limits on travelers who have visited Iran and recommended against travel to hard-hit areas of Italy and South Korea.
snippet: The United States is considering shutting the country's southern border with Mexico to control the spread of the new coronavirus, President Donald Trump said on Saturday, as his administration announced new limits on travelers who have visited Ira...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States is considering shutting the country's southern border with Mexico to control the spread of the new coronavirus, President Donald Trump said on Saturday, as his administration announced new limits on travelers who have visited Iran and recommended against travel to hard-hit areas of Italy and South Korea.
headline_main: Trump Says U.S. Considering Restrictions at Mexican Border Over Coronavirus
headline_print_headline: Trump Says U.S. Considering Restrictions at Mexican Border Over Coronavirus

abstract: Investors are looking to the Federal Reserve and its peers as markets swoon and infections rise. They’re short on ammunition.
snippet: Investors are looking to the Federal Reserve and its peers as markets swoon and infections rise. They’re short on ammunition.
lead_paragraph: Federal Reserve officials and their global counterparts are staring down an economic threat unlike any they have ever faced, as markets look to them to contain the fallout from a rapidly spreading virus with limited ammunition and tools ill-suited to deal with broken supply chains and quarantined consumers.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump, who earlier this week described the risk from the new coronavirus as "very low" in the United States, said he will hold a White House press conference about the fast-spreading flu-like illness at 1:30 pm EST (18:30 GMT) on Saturday.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump, who earlier this week described the risk from the new coronavirus as "very low" in the United States, said he will hold a White House press conference about the fast-spreading flu-like illness at 1:30 pm EST (18:30 GMT) on Saturday.
headline_main: Trump to Hold Press Conference on Coronavirus on Saturday in White House
headline_print_headline: Trump to Hold Press Conference on Coronavirus on Saturday in White House
